@node "System" "System requirements"
@{b}System requirements@{ub}

  To use AHelp you need at least an Amiga or WinUAE with harddisk
  and at least Workbench 2.04. 

  You also need NewInstaller v1.5 to install AHelp to your harddisk.
  NewInstaller v1.5 can be downloaded from Aminet (util/wb/NewInstaller1_5.lha)
  or my homepage (http://airsoft.home.pages.de).

  AHelp optionally requires guigfx.library and render.library by Timm S.
  Müller aswell as reqtools.library by Nico Francois. You can get them on
  Aminet. Guigfx.library and render.library need at least OS3.0 and a MC68020. 
  So you should also have such a system.

  If you want to view HTML documentations you need openurl.library by
  Troels Walsted Hansen. You can get this library on Aminet either.

  Amigaguide.library is also necessary but it`s delivered with the Workbench
  so everyone should have it.

@endnode

@node "ques" "Usage"
@{b}Usage@{ub}

  The main program: AHelp
  =======================

  To start AHelp, doubleclick the icon and press HELP (or your defined
  CX_POPKEY).

  Now a nice GUI appears. If you click on an entry in the ListView gadget
  the document/guide will be viewed.

  The following buttons are in the GUI:

  Preferences: This button starts the preferences program of AHelp. You
               can define all tooltype options from the preferences
               program.

  About: This button displays some information about AHelp.

  Exit: This button quits AHelp.

  If you want the GUI iconify, press ESC (or your defined CX_ICONKEY).
  AHelp iconifies then and displays an app icon on your Workbench
  (only if you`ve set the CX_APPICON tooltype). AHelp will also add
  itself to the tools menu of the Workbench.


  The preferences program: AHelp Prefs
  ====================================

  Notes: - You can also set all options in the tooltypes of AHelp. If you
           do so you do not need to use the preferences program!
  
         - The AHelp Preferences program needs at least MUI3.8!       

  To start AHelp Prefs, doubleclick the icon.

  Now a GUI appears. You can select now between different options:

  Add AppIcon: If you select "yes" in this cycle gadget, AHelp will add
               an AppIcon to your Workbench.

  Close gadget ends AHelp: If you select "yes" in this cycle gadget, AHelp
                           will quit if you press the close gadget. Otherwise
                           it will iconify.

  Popup at start: If you set this cycle gadget to "yes", AHelp will open
                  its window after it was started. Otherwise it will open
                  in iconified mode.

  Popup key: In this string gadget you can type in the hotkey (combination)
             that will open AHelp. For example: "help" or "alt h".

  Iconify key: In this string gadget you can type in the hotkey (combination)
               that will iconify AHelp. For example "esc" or "alt i".

  Help path: Here you can select the path, where your help files are stored
             in. Normally this is "Help:".

  Viewer for guides: Here you can select the viewer for the guide files in
                     your help directory. You can use the variable "%f" for
                     the filename. If you don`t activate this field, AHelp
                     will use amigaguide.library for viewing the guides.

  Viewer for others: Here you can select the viewer for all other files in
                     your help directory. You can use the variable "%f" for
                     the filename. If you don`t activate this field, AHelp
                     will use amigaguide.library for viewing.

  Save: If you click this button, AHelp will save the preferences.

  About: Displays some information about the preferences program.

  Quit: Exits the application.

@endnode

@node "history" "History"
@{b}History@{ub}

  V1.5: (Freeware Release Version)

  · Most of the suggestions in this release were made by Olivier Fabre. Thanks!
  · Updated Installer; requires now NewInstaller v1.5 (Aminet: util/wb/NewInstaller1_5.lha)
  · Updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · Some changes in AHelp Prefs
  · Updated Spanish catalog by Damaso Dominguez
  · Updated French catalog by Didier Giron
  · Updated German catalog
  · Added new catalog description and translation files
  · Some other changes/improvements
  · Fixed some bugs that could occur when using Exchange to control AHelp
  · AHelp accepts return key now also as input in the listview
  · Preferences button in AHelp is now enabled and starts AHelp preferences
    if it has been clicked
  · Completely reprogrammed the preferences program for AHelp. It uses MUI
    now and is more flexible than the old, buggy Gadtools one
  · Redesigned the AHelp logo. Boing ball looks better now
  · Removed NOGUIGFX tooltype. AHelp recognizes now itself if guigfx is present
  · Improved the library code; should work now on every Amiga system
  · Fixed some problems with the hotkeys
  · AHelp opens now in the center of the screen

  V1.4: (Freeware Release Version)

  · Updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · Works now with Visual Prefs (therefore the VISUALPREFS tooltype has been
    removed)
  · Appicon is now included in the executable

  V1.3: (Freeware Release Version)

  · Some minor changes/improvements
  · Keyboards shortcuts work now in the GUI
  · Updated and localized installer script
  · Updated AmigaGuide® documentation
  · Prefs program isn`t needed any longer, edit the tooltypes by yourself
  · Some bugfixes
  · Added new tooltypes NOGUIGFX, VIEWERGUIDE & VIEWEROTHER
  · Added french catalog by Lionel <thillot.lionel@accesinternet.com>
  · Added french catalog by Didier Giron <girondid@fnac.net>
  · Added spanish catalog by Damaso Dominguez <amidde@arrakis.es>

  V1.2: (Freeware Release Version)

  · Updated Installation script
  · Updated AmigaGuide® documentation 
  · new tooltype: VISUALPREFS. Set it if you use Visual Prefs
    and experience problems with AHelp
  · added fontsensitivity code to AHelp Preferences program
  · turned MUI interface in a fully fontsensitive and resizable
    gadtools GUI
  · added locale.library and a german catalog aswell as the developer
    files
  · added nice logo to the GUI which is automatically remapped to
    Workbench palette (this job is done by guigfx.library)
  · relayouted the GUI
  · GUI is now controllable by keyboard either
  · some visual changes
  · added support for HTML files (this job is done by openurl.library)
  · normal documentations are now viewed with amigaguide.library instead
    of Sys:Utilities/Multiview...
  · alot of code optimizations
  · turned listview into a little directory browser
  · recoded commodity/app handler
  · AHelp is now added to the Tools menu of the Workbench when it`s
    iconified

  V1.1: (Internal Beta)

  · MUI version

  V1.0: (Freeware Release Version)

  · AHelp Prefs V1.0
  · runs as a commodity
  · MWB icons (done by The Falconer)
  · reqtools.library (© Niço François) support 
  · Install script
  · AmigaGuide® Documentation

  Future plans:

  Not much....If you miss something in AHelp please contact me!

  And always remember...The future is still unwritten...

@endnode

 
 
